'''Bernard Dell''' (born 1949) is an [[Australians|Australian]] [[botanist]]. He is a research director at [[Murdoch University]] developing strategic research partnerships with China and nearby countries. His research spans the disciplines of [[agriculture]] and [[forestry]]. He is the author of books<ref name="jarrah">{{cite book|last1=Dell|first1=Bernard|last2=Havel,|first2=J.J.|last3=Malajczuk|first3=N.|title=The jarrah forest : a complex mediterranean ecosystem|date=1989|publisher=Kluwer Academic Publishers|location=Dordrecht|isbn=9061936586}}</ref> and academic papers<ref name="loop">{{cite web|title=Bernard Dell|url=http://loop.frontiersin.org/people/156754/overview|publisher=Loop|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="CMU">{{cite web|title=CMU Scholarly Research Report|url=http://library.cmu.ac.th/scholarly/index.php?AfID=60000881&Author=7004909808|publisher=Chiang Mai University|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="PubFacts">{{cite web|title=Publications authored by Bernard Dell|url=http://www.pubfacts.com/author/Bernard+Dell|publisher=PubFacts|accessdate=7 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=TIKjHokAAAAJ&hl=en|title=Bernard Dell - Google Scholar Citations|website=scholar.google.com.au|access-date=2018-02-16}}</ref> on these subjects and is the recipient of a Murdoch University Excellence in Research Award (2012), the [[Friendship Award (China)|China Friendship Award]] (2014) and the [[Chiang Mai University]] Award (2015).<ref name="Murdoch(1)">{{cite web|title=Murdoch research professor wins China honour|url=http://media.murdoch.edu.au/murdoch-research-professor-wins-china-honour|publisher=Murdoch University|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="Murdoch(2)">{{cite web|title=Professor Bernard Dell|url=http://profiles.murdoch.edu.au/myprofile/bernard-dell/|publisher=Murdoch University|accessdate=7 March 2016}}</ref>

