{{Use British English|date=November 2017}}
'''Quality Meat Scotland''' ('''QMS''') is an [[executive non-departmental public body]] of the [[Scottish Government]]. It promotes the [[red meat]] sector and markets the [[Protected Geographical Indication]] '''Scotch Beef''' and '''Scotch Lamb''' brands.

It was set up in 1990 to provide assurance to industry and consumers that animals produced for the food chain met certain standards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sfqc.co.uk/assurance-schemes/livestock-and-dairy/quality-meat-scotland-qms-assurance-scheme-cattle-and-sheep/ |title=Quality Meat Scotland (QMS) Assurance Scheme - Cattle and Sheep |publisher=SFQC (Scottish Food Quality Certification Ltd) |accessdate=24 September 2014}}</ref>

